🌞 Forever passionate about the process! 3 - 5yrs broken down to 1min ! 

 The heart of Foundation lives in the dark, dense soil of Estelí, where tobacco seeds begin their long journey to becoming award-winning cigars.  Foundation has released a time-lapse video sharing the extensive process about how their cigars are made. To accompany the abridged 1min version, Foundation also has the full length 10minute video on our YouTube channel !  #foundationcigars #cigarlife #seedtocigar #cigaraficionado #cigarpress #cigarsnob #cigarloversmagazine #cigars #cigar

2yrs ago this month @thereminders met @nickragua & @thiefoperandi in Esteli, Nicaragua to shoot a music video for our annual trade show @pca1933 ! The Reminders sent the track to Nick in May and a month later we were riding a creative wave and the video was born! Special thanks to @kenneth_espinoza07 for 🎥 filming this music video ! We all had a lot of fun…. 
2021 could we see a follow up video ? Time will tell ! #foundationcigars #thereminders #cigars #esteli #nicaragua #musicvideo #anthem

node.text:
The heart of Foundation 🌞 lives in the dark, dense volcanic 🌋 soil of Estelí, where tobacco seeds begin their long journey to becoming award-winning cigars. This 11-minute time-lapse spans an entire year, though the whole process to create every part of Foundation’s cigars can take 2-4 years, with long fermentation periods. This video breaks down the handmade craft into a number of steps, from seed beds, to curing, productions, molds, quality control, and more. It’s a fascinating look inside a remarkable art form and  showcases the many people involved from beginning to end....
Esteli, amante del presente. Forjador del futuro. #foundationcigars #cigarlife #Esteli #Nicaragua #Connecticut #cigars #handmade

node.text:
*Available August 17th via @jrcigars ! **Only 500 boxes Made !🌞 🌋 

The list of 50th Anniversary collaborators for @jrcigars continues to grow as they have teamed up with industry icon @nickragua and his team at Foundation Cigars.  For this release, Nick has crafted a new version of Foundations first cigar, El Güegüense. 
 
El Güegüense, which translates to “Wise Man”, is Nicaraguan dramatic theater piece that dates back to the 16th Century, and is one of the oldest indigenous works in the Western Hemisphere. Nick Melillo chose the name in honor of his love for the country of Nicaragua and its people. 

This cigar is offered in a custom 10-count box, with a beautiful art piece on this inside of the covered.  The artwork was designed by the Foundation Art Director @thiefoperandi .  The cigar comes in one size: 6 ¼ X 46 Lonsdale and is based on the Güengüense 5yr Anniversario Blend. Only 500 boxes have been made. #foundationcigars #ElGüegüense #TheWiseMan #cigarlife #Esteli #Nicaragua #cigars
